<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1610">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/108.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Vice-Consul <persName type="to">Blocker</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 285.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                                telegram of January 31, 1915, reporting that you have refused to
                                certify invoices of coal entered for export to the United States by
                                the Constitutionalist authorities for the reason that the coal was
                                taken from the Rio Escondido and Agujita coal mines, owned by French
                                and American citizens.</p>
                            <p>Your action in the matter is approved by the Department.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>